  "text": "Macrophage activation in the DRG is necessary for the development of nociceptive hypersensitivity after nerve injury. [CITATION_1] ,29,41,72 Therefore, we investigated whether prior running would attenuate the expression of the macrophage marker Iba1 and the chemokine CCL2 in the ipsilateral lumbar DRG. Expression of Iba1, CD11b, and CCL2 was significantly increased at 3 and 14 days after CCI in the locked wheel controls (P , 0.05), and decreased at both time points by 6 weeks of voluntary wheel running ceasing before CCI (P , 0.05; Fig. 3A, B) .",
